HEADWORD: Senegin
<hw>Sen"e*gin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med. Chem.)</fld>
<def>A substance extracted from the rootstock of the <spn>Polygala
Senega</spn> (Seneca root), and probably identical with polygalic
acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

